Robust MQTT pattern:
```c
void mqtt_event_handler(void *arg, esp_event_base_t base, int32_t id, void *data) {
    switch (id) {
    case MQTT_EVENT_CONNECTED:
        is_connected = true;
        flush_offline_buffer(); // send queued messages
        resubscribe_topics();   // re-subscribe after reconnect
        break;
    case MQTT_EVENT_DISCONNECTED:
        is_connected = false;
        break;
    case MQTT_EVENT_ERROR:
        log_mqtt_error(data);
        break;
    }
}

// Offline buffer (ring buffer in RTC RAM survives deep sleep):
RTC_DATA_ATTR OfflineMsg_t offline_buf[32];
void publish_or_buffer(const char *topic, const char *payload) {
    if (is_connected) {
        esp_mqtt_client_publish(client, topic, payload, 0, 1, 0);
    } else {
        ring_push(&offline_buf, topic, payload);
    }
}
```
Set `clean_session=false` for persistent subscriptions. Use QoS 1+ for reliable delivery.

